// ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ Audit Log ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

model AuditLog {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId    String?  @map("user_id")
  action    String // e.g. "auth.login", "measurement.create", "export.csv"
  details   String? // JSON string, no sensitive data
  ipAddress String?  @map("ip_address")
  location  String? // e.g. "Berlin, DE" ‚Äî resolved from IP at log time
  // v1.4.27 B3 ‚Äî resolved at audit-creation time from the bundled
  // GeoLite2-ASN MMDB. `asn` is the autonomous-system number,
  // `carrier` is the organisation string (e.g. "Deutsche Telekom AG").
  // Both nullable so older rows, private-IP rows, and offline-miss
  // rows stay valid.
  asn       Int? // autonomous-system number
  carrier   String? // autonomous-system organisation
  createdAt DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")

  user User? @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: SetNull)

  @@index([userId, createdAt])
  @@index([action, createdAt])
  // v1.12.1 (P1-2) ‚Äî status-cache reads filter `{ userId, action }`
  // ordered by `createdAt desc` on every insight-status card mount;
  // this three-column index serves both the findFirst and the take:5 as
  // an index range scan over the highest-churn table. See migration 0123.
  @@index([userId, action, createdAt(sort: Desc)])
  @@map("audit_logs")
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ Notification System ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

model NotificationChannel {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId    String   @map("user_id")
  type      String // "TELEGRAM" | "NTFY" | "WEB_PUSH" | "APNS"
  enabled   Boolean  @default(true)
  config    String // AES-256-GCM encrypted JSON (channel-specific config)
  createdAt DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")
  updatedAt DateTime @updatedAt @map("updated_at")

  // ‚îÄ‚îÄ v1.4.15 Phase B3: reliability fields ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ
  // Reason the channel was auto-disabled (e.g. "hard_reject_410",
  // "telegram_blocked_by_user", "telegram_chat_not_found",
  // "give_up_after_5_failures"). NULL when the channel is healthy
  // OR was disabled manually (in which case `enabled=false` alone
  // is enough ‚Äî no automated process should treat that as
  // re-enable-able).
  disabledReason      String?   @map("disabled_reason")
  consecutiveFailures Int       @default(0) @map("consecutive_failures")
  lastSuccessAt       DateTime? @map("last_success_at")
  lastFailureAt       DateTime? @map("last_failure_at")
  lastFailureReason   String?   @map("last_failure_reason")
  // The next time the dispatcher is allowed to attempt a send for
  // this channel after a transient failure. NULL = no cooldown.
  // Hard rejects flip `enabled=false` instead of writing this.
  nextRetryAt         DateTime? @map("next_retry_at")

  user        User                     @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)
  preferences NotificationPreference[]

  @@unique([userId, type])
  @@index([userId])
  @@map("notification_channels")
}

model NotificationPreference {
  id        String  @id @default(cuid())
  channelId String  @map("channel_id")
  eventType String  @map("event_type") // "MEDICATION_REMINDER" | "MEASUREMENT_ANOMALY" | etc.
  enabled   Boolean @default(true)

  channel NotificationChannel @relation(fields: [channelId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@unique([channelId, eventType])
  @@map("notification_preferences")
}

model PushSubscription {
  id        String   @id @default(cuid())
  userId    String   @map("user_id")
  endpoint  String
  p256dh    String // encrypted
  auth      String // encrypted
  userAgent String?  @map("user_agent")
  createdAt DateTime @default(now()) @map("created_at")

  user User @relation(fields: [userId], references: [id], onDelete: Cascade)

  @@unique([userId, endpoint])
  @@index([userId])
  @@map("push_subscriptions")
}

// ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ Data Backups ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ

model DataBackup {
